snippet.textDisplay: I have owned an Audi RS4 and Nissan R35 GTR and loved them both. But for 95% of the time in every day driving I prefer my Model 3 P. It is quiet, stealth fast, smooth, safe, quite spacious and has the most comfortable seats and best audio I have experienced in a car. I charge it off roof top solar, it doesn't require servicing, and costs almost nothing to run. Sure, the GTR is faster over 100 mph and quicker round a track. But it's no contest when choosing a car for real world driving.

snippet.textDisplay:
In the end, the Tesla still looks and sounds like sh!t! The interior is an absolute joke. It’s completely forgettable. So I blow “performance” cars away stop light to stop light or occasionally bash my passenger’s heads against the headrest after quick take-off (my wife hates this)? The point is, it’s a quick sudden fleeting thrill and little else, or a quick “jerk” if you will.

I know, Green is good for the planet, so buy one of the lower powered and cheaper versions for your work commute (or by a cheap hybrid something that won’t leave you searching for chargers), but don’t sell that great sounding older performance convertible just yet; you’ll miss it for real auto thrills.

Please save your breath selling me on Tesla on how incredibly fast they are, because I truly don’t care! I’m an auto enthusiast.
